<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idcf66e129-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0" identifier="/us/usc/t48/s916"><num value="916">§ 916.</num><heading> Ratification of previous legislation</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">All legislation heretofore enacted by the Legislature of Puerto Rico dealing with the subject matter of sections 911 to 916 of this title and not inconsistent herewith is ratified and confirmed.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idcf66e12a-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0">(<ref href="/us/act/1938-06-25/ch703/s6">June 25, 1938, ch. 703, § 6</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/52/1203">52 Stat. 1203</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idcf66e12b-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="idcf66e12c-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I76" topic="codification" id="idcf66e12d-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Codification</heading>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section was not enacted as part of the Puerto Rican Federal Relations Act which comprises this chapter.</p>
</note>
</notes>
</section>
